-- 1. [Problem Restatement] Factor 10x² − x − 24 as (Ax − 8)(Bx + 3) with integers A, B and evaluate AB + B. 2. [Key Idea] Expand (Ax − 8)(Bx + 3) and match its coefficients with 10x² − x − 24; the resulting system AB = 10 and 3A − 8B = −1 uniquely fixes A and B. 3. [Proof] Expand: (Ax − 8)(Bx + 3) = AB x² + (3A − 8B)x − 24. Match coefficients with 10x² − x − 24: (i) AB = 10 (ii) 3A − 8B = −1. Since AB = 10, possible integer pairs (A, B) are (1,10), (2,5), (5,2), (10,1) (or both negative but the second equation would fail to give −1). Test: • (1,10): 3·1 − 8·10 = −77 ≠ −1. • (2,5): 6 − 40 = −34 ≠ −1. • (5,2): 15 − 16 = −1 ✓. • (10,1): 30 − 8 = 22 ≠ −1. Thus A = 5 and B = 2. Compute: AB + B = 10 + 2 = 12. 4. [Conclusion] The required value is 12.
